4.2.1. The Competing Small a-C(:H) Evolution Scenarios
"The strong spatial variability of the aromatic feature strength
has been known for several decades. Dramatic variations have
been observed within Galactic and Magellanic H ii regions (e.g.
Boulanger et al. 1998; Madden et al. 2006; Galametz et al. 2013),
as well as among nearby galaxies (e.g. Galliano et al. 2003, 2005;
Engelbracht et al. 2005; Madden et al. 2006). The following sce-
narios have been proposed."
"Photodestruction. The aromatic feature strength appears to
be negatively correlated with the presence of intense/hard
UV fields. For instance, Boulanger et al. (1998) showed
that their strength in Galactic PDRs is decreasing when the
intensity of the ISRF is increasing. Madden et al. (2006)
showed that their strength, within Galactic and Magellanic re-
gions and within nearby galaxies, is negatively correlated with
[Ne iii]15.56µm/[Ne ii]12.81µm, an ISRF hardness indicator. Numer-
ous studies confirmed these trends, showing the depletion of aro-"
