quantities of a given galaxy, such as the dust and stellar masses,
were usually explained with different values of the dust evolu-
tion parameters, at different ages. On the contrary, our approach
allows us to avoid mutually inconsistent explanations of different
trends and correlations. Overall, performing a rigorous fit does
not help getting better solutions, but it definitely helps avoiding
bad ones."
