Appendix A: CALIBRATION UNCERTAINTIES
"The HB approach is one of the only methods allowing a rigorous
treatment of the photometric calibration uncertainties. These un-
certainties are indeed systematic effects, with both spectral and
spatial correlations. Some studies account for their spectral cor-
relations, but ignore their spatial correlations (e.g. Gordon et al.
2014). In the present paper, following G18, we assume that cal-
ibration uncertainties are perfectly correlated between sources,
and partially correlated between wavelengths. In this section, we
discuss the values of these uncertainties and of their correlation
coefficients."
