"Appendix G: DUST EVOLUTION RESULTS
ASSUMING A CHABRIER IMF"
"We have performed the modelling of Sect. 5.2.2, assuming a
Chabrier (2003) IMF. The data have been corrected accordingly:
M? has been multiplied by 0.61 and SFR by 0.63 (Madau &
Dickinson 2014), as these two quantities were derived assum-
ing a Salpeter (1955) IMF. Fig. G.1 shows the fit of the scaling
relations; it is the equivalent of Fig. 14. Figs. G.2 – G.3 dis-
play the PDF of the dust evolution and SFH-related parameters,
respectively; they are the equivalent of Figs. 16 – 17. The in-
ferred timescales are displayed in Fig. G.4; it is the equivalent of
Fig. 18."
